        public int handleMove​(int score)
        Description copied from interface: goosegame.Cell
        returns the index of the cell really reached by a player when the player reaches this cell. For normal cells, the returned value equals getIndex() and is thus independent from diceThrow.
        Specified by:
        handleMove in interface goosegame.Cell
        Overrides:
        handleMove in class goosegame.NormalCell
        Parameters:
        score - the result of the dice when the player reaches this cell
        Returns:
        the index of the new cell where the player will finally arrive. The GooseCell makes it move 2 times the score.
